I don't quite trust him on either, he's too eager about the government.  
Anyway, we've got a better, more free option here, so I suggest we try to recruit more people to here instead of going back to an even more fed-riddled site than before.

>Correlation between multiple posts, combined with internet traffic data? Would it be prudent to occasionally delete your ZeroNet and do fresh install?
Assuming you aren't stupid enough to let slip anything about your RL anywhere, it's probably overkill to do it regularly.
The state isn't going to try and find a random shitposter by trying to correlate posts and data sent through TOR. Only really necessary if you're Assange, Bradley Trannings, somebody of that caliber. To go through all that work, they must really want you, specifically.

>>688a2cf7-fbe8-4f0a-81e9-dc7932008334
ZeroNet's design is kinda meh. Too much reliance on Javascript, and its anonymization option of Tor isn't designed for P2P.  
If they'd gone with something based on pure html and I2P, it'd probably be more popular on /tech/. I'm also just here because it's the least shit option currently because all the others aren't quite there yet.
